getShortMessageOrLongMessageOrClazz

public List<Object> getShortMessageOrLongMessageOrClazz()
Gets the value of the shortMessageOrLongMessageOrClazz property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the shortMessageOrLongMessageOrClazz property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getShortMessageOrLongMessageOrClazz().add(newItem);
